<head><meta charset="UTF-8"><title>PP Bag & Big-Bag Recycling — Igor Kryazhev</title><style>body{font-family:Arial,sans-serif;line-height:1.7;max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto;padding:40px;}</style></head>
<body><h1>Processing PP Bags and Big-Bags: MFI Control and Fiber Filtration</h1><p><strong>Author: Igor Kryazhev</strong></p><h2>Technical Challenges</h2><p>Oriented PP fibers have a high melting point. To prevent screen clogging, temperatures in the melting zone must be increased to 230-250°C with 0.4% antioxidant stabilization.</p></body></html>
